Binary crate root for `ctx-cage`'s CLI entrypoint (`ctx-run`), the process that wraps a user command in the sandbox and drives the post-run summarization workflow. Anything depending on ctx-cage as a library goes through the `cage` crate directly; this directory is the executable wiring, not the sandboxing logic itself.

`env_file.rs` is the only child file: it isolates a single, narrow concern — loading an optional, permission-checked credentials file (`CTX_AGENT_CMD`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`) used only to configure the summarizer step after the sandboxed command finishes. Its output never reaches the sandboxed command's environment or shell; that separation (summarizer config vs. sandboxed-process config) is the one invariant worth preserving if more config loading is added here — don't let the two channels merge.

No rollup for subdirectories exists because there's a single leaf file; if `main.rs` or other CLI-wiring files exist alongside it, they aren't yet documented here.

intent_divergence: no intent.md exists for this directory, so no claim can be checked against it.